EQ-5D was licensed for this study by EuroQol who adapted the tool for both Ugandan English and Luganda.

Within each of the five health domains, language was designed to be accessible to the target population (Ugandan TB survivors). 
In English, the domains were translated as follows:
MOBILITY - "walking around"
SELF-CARE - "washing or dressing yourself"
USUAL ACTIVITIES - "doing your ususal activiites"
PAIN/DISCOMFORT - "having pain or discomfort"
ANXIETY/DEPRESSION - "being worried or unhappy"
